    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "```cython\r\n    def in_cython_code(x):\r\n        print(x);\r\n```\r\nThis is such an easy mistake to make in a Python/Cython/C/C++ context that Cython should emit a warning when that happens.\r\n\r\nCan't say how difficult it would be to implement this. Might be a simple change in `Scanning.py` (or `Parsing.py`?) that automatically detects a semicolon before an EOL. Outside of strings, obviously. :)",
